headline_main: Stunning Turns in the Kavanaugh Drama
headline_print_headline: Stunning Turns in the Kavanaugh Drama

abstract: They took turns before the Senate Judiciary Committee, moving from sad certitude to angry umbrage.
snippet: They took turns before the Senate Judiciary Committee, moving from sad certitude to angry umbrage.
lead_paragraph: • Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh, President Trump’s Supreme Court nominee, came out swinging in the early moments of his testimony to senators, saying, “This confirmation process has become a national disgrace.”

abstract: The next generation of quarterbacks looks amazing. The old generation is not too bad, either. Here’s what happened around the league.
snippet: The next generation of quarterbacks looks amazing. The old generation is not too bad, either. Here’s what happened around the league.
lead_paragraph: An overtime thriller, multiple N.F.L. records, a devastating injury and one of the biggest upsets in N.F.L. history. Week 3 certainly kept the action coming. Here’s what we learned.

abstract: Now it is Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh who faces a hearing to address explosive accusations by Christine Blasey Ford that he sexually assaulted her when they were teenagers.
snippet: Now it is Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh who faces a hearing to address explosive accusations by Christine Blasey Ford that he sexually assaulted her when they were teenagers.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — She went public just days before a critical vote and took a polygraph test to bolster her credibility. He unequivocally denied her years-old charges of sexual misconduct. Calls mounted to delay the vote and investigate. It was late September, and a Supreme Court seat hung in the balance.

abstract: Even minor misdemeanor convictions are keeping some migrant parents from being reunited with their children, who must remain in federal shelters.
snippet: Even minor misdemeanor convictions are keeping some migrant parents from being reunited with their children, who must remain in federal shelters.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — A court-imposed deadline for reuniting “tender-age” children separated from their parents at the border came and went long ago. But a 3-year-old girl from El Salvador is going on her sixth month in a federal immigration shelter, one of dozens of migrant children stranded in the system because authorities have determined they cannot be returned to their parents.

abstract: Projects from these up-and-coming photographers are being displayed on four-foot wooden cubes at this year’s Photoville beneath the Brooklyn Bridge.
snippet: Projects from these up-and-coming photographers are being displayed on four-foot wooden cubes at this year’s Photoville beneath the Brooklyn Bridge.
lead_paragraph: Twelve up-and-coming photographers from Africa, Latin America and the United States are featured this month at Photoville, the temporary village of galleries in converted shipping containers underneath the Brooklyn Bridge.

abstract: Aaron Rodgers thrilled in a comeback. Tom Brady didn’t need to. The Cowboys might be in trouble. Here’s what happened in Week 1.
snippet: Aaron Rodgers thrilled in a comeback. Tom Brady didn’t need to. The Cowboys might be in trouble. Here’s what happened in Week 1.
lead_paragraph: • Aaron Rodgers only needs one leg to win. He was playing through a serious knee injury, his team was down 17 points at the start of the fourth quarter, and the Chicago Bears seemed much-improved on both sides of the ball. But Rodgers got the ball back with 2:39 left to play and the Bears had lost the game even before Rodgers hit Randall Cobb for a 75-yard go-ahead touchdown, they just didn’t know it yet.
